<h4>Position Description:</h4>  
<p>RDSI is seeking a full-time Human Resources (HR) Manager in its Middletown, RI location. The successful candidate will report directly to the President, or the Vice President of Operations and work closely with their corporate counterparts. The HR Manager will be responsible for all Human Resources related matters and ensure that company policies and procedures to comply with state and federal guidelines and regulations.</p>

<!-- Responsibility Header -->
<h4>Responsibilities:</h4>
<!-- Responsibility bullets -->
	<h4 style="margin-left: 20px">Team Member Relations:</h4>
    <ul>
    	<li style="margin-left: 30px">Serve as a link between management and team members by handling questions, 	interpreting and administrating corporate policies and helping to resolve work-related issues..</li> 
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Maintain in-house job descriptions and oversee Performance Evaluation process.</li>
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Develop and conduct hiring procedures for all company personnel.</li>
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Conduct voluntary and involuntary termination procedures for all company personnel.</li>
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Oversee worker's compensation claims processing and coordination between employee and insurance carrier.</li>
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Manage all employee relations issues and conduct fair, unbiased, and compliant investigations. Provide advice to management and coaching to employees and managers as necessary.</li>
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Handle escalated issues related to all personnel related polices</li>
        </ul>
    <h4 style="margin-left: 20px">Benefits:</h4>
    <ul>
    	<li style="margin-left: 30px">Working with their corporate counterpart, analyze and modify compensation and benefits policies to establish competitive programs and ensure compliance with legal requirements.</li> 
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Benchmark RDSI Benefits and Compensation Package as compared to local competitors. Provide recommendations to the President to maintain a completive Compensation Plan.</li>
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Working with their corporate counterparts, review the benefits package and provide recommendations to include annual re-evaluation of policies for cost effectiveness and employee satisfaction, review of renewal of bids from insurers and brokers, make recommendations to management, and conduct open enrollment meetings.</li>

     </ul>
    <h4 style="margin-left: 20px">Compliance:</h4>
	<ul>
    	<li style="margin-left: 30px">Monitor Department of Labor rules and regulations, as well as other federal, multi-state and case law changes, regulatory updates, and other legislative issues, and advise management on any necessary actions.</li> 
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Maintain Affirmative Action/EEO/VETS programs; files EEO-1/VETS and other DOL reports annually and as required; maintain other records, reports, and logs to conform to applicable regulations.</li>
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Direct the administration of the safety and recreation programs.</li>
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Develop and recommend new or updated personnel policies and procedures to senior management for approval; maintain employee handbook.</li>

     </ul>
    <h4 style="margin-left: 20px">Recruitment:</h4>
	<ul>
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Develop formal recruiting and retention process and new team member on boarding program.</li>
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Working with the President, establish Succession Planning Guidelines
		Establish Strategic Hire Guidelines.</li>
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Oversee maintenance of organizational documentation such as Organizational Charts, Newsletters, required posters, personnel files, etc.</li>
		<li style="margin-left: 30px">Conduct HR staff meetings and organize other employee training meetings as needed.</li>
	</ul>
	<br></br>
    

